    "The underlying machine learning model used may vary [e.g., support vector machine (SVM), naïve Bayes, neural network, etc.",
    "], but the framework involves learning the relationship between certain input features (usually molecular or peptide descriptors) and the activity potency (or, more generally, any chemical property) (Fig. 3).",
    "For fighting AMR and identifying new potential drugs, predictive ML models have been shown to be effective in predicting biological activity of both small molecule antibiotics 5, 20, 81 and AMPs 22, 79, 82.",
    "They may also be used to predict secondary properties relevant to drug candidates such as solubility, toxicity, etc.",
    "More recently, deep learning models which rely on automatically learned features instead of pre-defined molecular descriptors have been developed for predicting various properties of small molecules and peptides."
